{
  "texts": [
    "IS measures the lowest score as 1 while the highest score depends on the number of classes of the dataset.",
    "The higher IS score shows that the model can generate high-quality as well as diverse images.",
    "The maximum mean discrepancy is used to measure the dissimilarity between real image distribution p r and generated image distribution p g (Gretton et al. 2012).",
    "The higher value of MMD indicates that the generator is collapsing and doesn't generate realistic and diverse images.",
    "Mathematically, it uses Hilbert's space of functions."
  ]
}